6. start()

Purpose

Tell Salesforce

Which records should I process?

Example

global Database.QueryLocator start(Database.BatchableContext bc)
{
    return Database.getQueryLocator(
        'SELECT Id, Name FROM Account'
    );
}

Salesforce stores this query. Later it divides the records.

Why QueryLocator?

Normal SOQl -> 50,000 records

Batch QueryLocator -> 50 Million records

Huge difference.

